---
// One idea: the body's first lesson is the safe fall, not the graceful stand.
---
<svg width="600" height="240" viewBox="0 0 600 240" role="img" aria-labelledby="fall-t">
  <title id="fall-t">A hard vertical drop that would jar is redrawn as a rolling curve that meets the ground softly; the soft curve is marked in the accent colour.</title>
  <!-- ground -->
  <path class="ink block" d="M40 196 C 220 188, 400 188, 560 196" />
  <!-- the feared fall: a stiff drop -->
  <path class="ink hair" d="M140 44 L 140 186" stroke-dasharray="3 6" opacity="0.6" />
  <path class="ink hair" d="M128 172 L 140 190 L 152 172" opacity="0.6" />
  <text class="hand-label" x="86" y="40" font-size="16" opacity="0.7">the braced fall</text>
  <!-- the learned fall: a roll -->
  <path class="ink spine" d="M300 50 C 322 96, 300 140, 344 168 C 384 192, 460 186, 512 190" stroke="var(--poppy)" />
  <circle class="port-ring" cx="300" cy="50" r="9" />
  <circle class="port-fill" cx="300" cy="50" r="3.4" />
  <text class="hand-label hand-label--accent" x="352" y="128" font-size="18">roll, don&rsquo;t brace</text>
  <text class="hand-label" x="452" y="180" font-size="16">soft landing</text>
</svg>
